cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.SP 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper investigates the capability of mmWave channel sounders with phased arrays to perform super-resolution parameter estimation, which involves analyzing the information content of the received signals. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on the performance of a novel multi-beam mmWave channel sounder that is capable of performing MIMO measurements in dynamic environments, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a novel two-step calibration procedure that provides higher-accuracy calibration data, which is relevant to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper investigates the performance of a sounder that is capable of measuring and analyzing signals in the mmWave frequency range, which is relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.SP (Signal Processing): The paper analyzes the impact of center misalignment and residual phase noise on the performance of the parameter estimator, which is relevant to signal processing.
